00:14:50.500 --> 00:14:52.260
I like ROI.

00:14:52.260 --> 00:14:54.020
It's a great efficiency metric.

00:14:56.620 --> 00:15:00.710
Usually you try to maximize
your ROI up until the point

00:15:00.710 --> 00:15:02.590
where it's below
some sort of hourly

00:15:02.590 --> 00:15:05.810
that you set for
yourself, because one

00:15:05.810 --> 00:15:08.970
of the ways you supplement ROI
is by moving down in stakes.

00:15:08.970 --> 00:15:11.140
Usually lower stakes
are easier games.

00:15:11.140 --> 00:15:13.110
You should have a
higher win rate.

00:15:13.110 --> 00:15:17.700
But that win rate's multiplied
by a much lower number.

00:15:17.700 --> 00:15:21.380
So usually you're going to move
around in stakes until you have

00:15:21.380 --> 00:15:24.810
a good ROI, but hopefully above
what you consider your lowest

00:15:24.810 --> 00:15:28.871
amount that you can feel
comfortable earning.

00:15:28.871 --> 00:15:30.870
In addition, I want to
focus on live tournaments

00:15:30.870 --> 00:15:33.970
because who knows what's
